result.solvingStrategy: The transformation involves identifying the positions of 5s in the input grid and replacing certain 0s with 2s based on their proximity to these 5s. Specifically, 0s that are directly below a 5 or directly above a 5 are replaced with 2s. The 5s themselves remain unchanged.
result.keySteps: 1. Analyze training examples to identify the pattern of 2s appearing in rows between rows containing 5s. 2. Observe that 2s are placed directly below and above 5s in the same column. 3. Apply this rule to the test case input by replacing 0s with 2s in positions directly adjacent (above and below) to 5s in the same column.
result.patternDescription: For each 5 in the input grid, replace the 0 directly below it and the 0 directly above it (if they exist) with 2s. The 5s remain unchanged.
hints: For each cell in the grid, if it contains a 5, set the cell directly below and above to 2 (if within bounds).
Math: For each (i,j) where grid[i][j] == 5, set grid[i-1][j] = 2 and grid[i+1][j] = 2 (if valid indices).
